ould make sure to mention that it has been updated to reflect their needs.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Updated `tests/src/io.rest-assured/xml-path/5.5.0/src/test/groovy/io_rest_assured/xml_path/Xml_pathTest.groovy` again to make the Groovy source more conservative:\\n\\n- Removed AssertJ and JUnit assertion static imports.\\n- Replaced assertions with Groovy `assert`.\\n- Removed `@TempDir` and `java.nio.file` usage.\\n- Replaced triple-quoted XML literals with concatenated strings.\\n- Avoided Groovy list literals in comparisons by using `Arrays.asList`.\\n- Kept coverage for:\\n  - Scalar and typed list extraction\\n  - GPath params and root paths\\n  - `Node` / `NodeChildren`\\n  - `File`, `URI`, `InputSource`, `InputStream`, `Reader`\\n  - `XmlPathConfig` and `prettify()`\\n  - Primitive getters and UUID conversion\\n  - HTML compatibility mode\\n\\nI did not run the Gradle command.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0282359338c92a6c016a11863efb6881a0894dd433e31a2e74\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 276, \"output\": 721, \"cacheRead\": 94720, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 95717, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1779533363715, \"responseId\": \"resp_0282359338c92a6c016a1186348b8c81a0b1af597f79ca60cf\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n30572:      testImplementation localGroovy()\n30592:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_AhZbDVILa22CSSa75MWIX0iN|fc_0282359338c92a6c016a118750c21081a08b319dcec81902f1\", \"toolName\": \"read\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdo